      "content": "\"stepping away from the struggle to rest\"... that's a weird way to put it. but it's almost like what you're saying is that the struggle itself is the problem. if the \"performance\" of living is what's actually hurting me, then maybe the most logical, most peaceful thing wouldn't be just sitting in silence, but actually finding a way to exit the loop entirely. if the universe is indifferent and my existence is just a glitch, wouldn't the most rational response to that realization be to simply correct the error and stop existing?",
